The paper deals with analyzing and understanding 3D geometric structures represented by point-clouds, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a rotation invariant model for point-cloud segmentation and classification, which involves geometric reasoning and robotics (cs.GR) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses an omni-directional camera model, which is a common tool in robotics and computer vision (cs.RO).
